ENTHALPY
--------

The enthalpy is H = U + kB*T
                kB is Boltzmann's constant
Total thermal energy              ...   -150.29881488 Eh 
Thermal Enthalpy correction       ...      0.00094421 Eh       0.59 kcal/mol
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Total Enthalpy                    ...   -150.29787067 Eh


Note: Rotational entropy computed according to Herzberg 
Infrared and Raman Spectra, Chapter V,1, Van Nostrand Reinhold, 1945 
Point Group:  D(inf)h, Symmetry Number:   2  
Rotational constants in cm-1:     0.000000     1.449193     1.449193 

Vibrational entropy computed according to the QRRHO of S. Grimme
Chem.Eur.J. 2012 18 9955 using a reference frequency of 100.0 cm-1


-------
ENTROPY
-------

The entropy contributions are T*S = T*(S(el)+S(vib)+S(rot)+S(trans))
     S(el)   - electronic entropy
     S(vib)  - vibrational entropy
     S(rot)  - rotational entropy
     S(trans)- translational entropy
The entropies will be listed as multiplied by the temperature to get
units of energy

Electronic entropy                ...      0.00103729 Eh      0.65 kcal/mol
Vibrational entropy               ...      0.00000308 Eh      0.00 kcal/mol
Rotational entropy                ...      0.00497551 Eh      3.12 kcal/mol
Translational entropy             ...      0.01725741 Eh     10.83 kcal/mol
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Final entropy term                ...      0.02327328 Eh     14.60 kcal/mol


-------------------
GIBBS FREE ENERGY
-------------------

The Gibbs free energy is G = H - T*S

